messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Summary of endpoints (prefix from index.js: app.use('/clients', clientRoutes)):

1) Path: /clients
- allMethods: false
- HEAD: false
- POST: true     (router.post('/', createClient))
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true      (router.get('/', getClients))
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

2) Path: /clients/user
- allMethods: false
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true      (router.get('/user', getClientsByUser))
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

3) Path: /clients/{id}
- allMethods: false
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false     (Note: controllers/clients.js exports getClient, but routes/clients.js does not register a GET for '/:id')
- PUT: false
- DELETE: true   (router.delete('/:id', deleteClient))
- PATCH: true    (router.patch('/:id', updateClient))

Explanation:
- index.js mounts the router with app.use('/clients', clientRoutes), so every path in routes/clients.js is prefixed with /clients.
- routes/clients.js explicitly registers these routes:
  - GET '/' -> getClients  (becomes GET /clients)
  - GET '/user' -> getClientsByUser  (becomes GET /clients/user)
  - POST '/' -> createClient  (becomes POST /clients)
  - PATCH '/:id' -> updateClient  (becomes PATCH /clients/{id})
  - DELETE '/:id' -> deleteClient  (becomes DELETE /clients/{id})
- Although controllers/clients.js exports getClient (which expects req.params.id), that function is never wired to any route in routes/clients.js, so GET /clients/{id} is not available.
- No explicit handlers for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT (except those listed), or "all methods" exist in the code. Per the instructions, the decision is based only on the code shown (i.e., only registered routes count), so these methods are marked false where not explicitly registered.
